     <h3>Paramparagat Krishi Vikas Yojana (PKVY)</h3>
     <h5>The Department of Agriculture and cooperation </h5>
     <p>Paramparagat Krishi Vikas Yojana (PKVY) is being implemented with a view to promote organic farming in the country. This will improve soil health and organic matter content and increase net income of the farmer so as to realise premium prices. Under this scheme, an area of 5 lakh acre is targeted to be covered though 10,000 clusters of 50 acre each, from the year 2015-16 to 2017-18.</p>
     </div>
